      "side": 1,
      "message": "Thanks a lot for catching this and for the EnvironmentMetrics pointer - that was a real semantic mismatch on my side.\nControl.Power.Cap (SetPoint / AllowableMin / AllowableMax) clearly belongs on EnvironmentMetrics.PowerLimitWatts as the mockup shows. To wire Chassis.MinPowerWatts / MaxPowerWatts up correctly, I have added MinPowerWatts / MaxPowerWatts to Inventory.Item.Accelerator (PDI 90569) for the device-spec power range, and this patch now reads from that interface instead. Thanks again for the careful review!\n\nhttps://gerrit.openbmc.org/c/openbmc/phosphor-dbus-interfaces/+/90569\nhttps://gerrit.openbmc.org/c/openbmc/dbus-sensors/+/90462",
